Data types
    data types in php
      String:
       - this is just plain text
       - to create we just use open-close quotation marks
      Numbers:
       Whole numbers
        - This is integer, can be positive or negative
       Decimal numbes
        - We define all number same way, but php internally will difference these
      Boolean:
       - This is just a tru/false value: true or false
      Resources:
       - This is a special variable holding a reference to an external resource of data
         such as:
         - stream(dir handle, file handle)
         - file
         - database(mysql, oracle, obdc)
         - socket
         - so on
       - example of resources => https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php-resources
      Objects:
       - This is an instance of a class!
      null:
       - This is a value stands for Not a value!
     


